laboratory_examinations.findings: CT abdomen pelvis with contrast showed a fluid-filled and dilated appendix measuring up to 10 mm, with subtle fat stranding, thickening of the lateral conal fascia, and a 0.5 cm appendicolith, consistent with early appendicitis. No focal fluid collection or extraluminal air was observed.
Creatinine level is 2.0 mg/dL, which is above the normal reference range of 1.6 - 2.6 mg/dL.
